A vintage 1950s advertising style illustration showing a frustrated person sitting at a mid-century modern desk, surrounded by a tangled mess of old telephone cords and cables that spiral outward like a chaotic web. The cables lead to nowhere, their ends frayed and disconnected, disappearing into empty wall sockets. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of retro advertisements. The person's expression conveys exasperation as they hold an old rotary telephone receiver, while papers with broken chain links illustrated on them scatter across the desk. In the background, a window shows a stylized cityscape with signal towers emitting dotted lines that abruptly stop mid-air, symbolizing broken connections.
